definition.value: A human embryonic stem cell line

HuH-7 is a well differentiated hepatocyte derived cellular carcinoma cell line that was originally taken from a liver tumor in a 57-year-old Japanese male in 1982. The line was established by Nakabayshi, H. and Sato, J. HuH-7 is an immortal cell line of epithelial-like tumorigenic cells. It usually grow in 2D monolayers.

Source : Pleural effusion, Ductal breast cancer (grade 3 invasive, T2N1M0)
Karyotype : Highly rearranged hyperdiploid karyotype with 6% polyploidy
Carry an amplified HER-2 oncogene and to be insensitive to HER-2-inhibiting drugs
